13 Tell him if the light with which your substance is adorned
14 will remain with you
15 eternally as it is now;

40 Its brightness follows the ardor;
41 the ardor, the vision; and that is as great
42 as the grace that exceeds its worth.

46 because that which the supreme good gives us
47 of gratuitous light will be increased,
48 light which conditions us to see him;

52 But just as a coal which renders flame,
53 and with its living whiteness conquers it,
54 so that its appearance is preserved;

55 so this lightning which now surrounds us
56 will be vanquished in appearance by the flesh
57 which every day the earth covers;

